snippet.textDisplay:
okay, but like connect this with the man who married a robot.

"The man and the internet went everywhere together
Except of course the places where the internet could not go
They went to the countryside, they went to birthday parties of the children of some of his less important friends, different countries, even the moon"

the moon was shown in the last part of the video, and I know that we all have different theories and interpretations, but here's mine. I think this is all about creating a relationship with the digital world (hence digital detox) rather than creating a relationship with those around you as well as nature itself (seems like we have a knack for digitally recreating nature, hence the mindshower, as we don't realize that nature is literally in front of us). this song symbolizes a person (most likely matty, or could be anyone) who goes to parties and social gatherings but instead of socializing, they become stuck to the phone. the phone and the internet becomes the captor, and the victim acquires stockholm syndrome. this song is literally one of the 1975's masterpieces. can't wait for notes!
